title: Fix GPA Calculation and Some UI Merge
message:
Fix GPA Calculation and Some UI Merge

Here I fixed a bug (before it was hard-coded to only calculate spring-semester gpas. Furthermore, it wrongly assumed that each semester class was worth 1 whole hour, so I changed it to .5 credits. Next, I also fixed cases where the imfamous NaN would occur if you had no spring semester grades. Finally, I decided to change the semester to an enum so that the semester values would be standard across (and I could stop using a boolean or an int to represent semester).

title: Fix a bug in DateHelper.timeSince method.
message:
Fix a bug in DateHelper.timeSince method.

First of all, I made sure that the number agreed with the time unit (i.e. 1 hour instead of 1 hours).
There was also a bug that would return "xxx hour less than a minute ago" where xxx was a number, because while the minute component was less than 0, the hour component would be non-zero. Now it should only return "xxx hour".

title: 1.  DataGrabber no longer implements Parcelable. Instead, it is stored in…
message:
1.  DataGrabber no longer implements Parcelable. Instead, it is stored in YourPISDApplication as instance variable. It can be used as a global variable using methods ( (YourPISDApplication) getApplication() ).setDataGrabber() and ( (YourPISDApplication) getApplication() ).getDataGrabber()
2.  Added student name parsing. This can be accessed by DataGrabber.getStudentName().

title: 1. Created MyApplication class. This will be used to store global variables…
message:
1. Created MyApplication class. This will be used to store global variables (like DataGrabber) so we don't have to parcel things around so much. I have not implemented this yet.
2. Inexplicably, the force close that used to occur when changing screen orientation on ClassSwipeActivity does not happen any more. However, the class order gets shuffled. I'm not sure what's causing this.

title: No more force close / timeout. Learned to use AsyncTask correctly.
message:
No more force close / timeout. Learned to use AsyncTask correctly.
Prototype stage is complete. Before we continue, we should plan out our app flow and data structures. Then, rewrite DataGrabber a bit.
BTW the reason that we use Fragments is so that data can be stored uninterrupted in an Activity. So, no data should be refreshed in the ClassSwipe DescriptionFragment.onCreateView. It should all be stored as class variables under ClassSwipe, not class variables in DescriptionFragment.
Also, ClassSwipe should be renamed to ClassSwipeActivity.
